hopobject.body: I study here thepillsquality.be reviews * JPMorgan is willing to pay a steep price to settlewith the Justice Department over soured mortgage securities, butit is getting one thing it wanted: It won't have to pay heavypenalties for the sins of two companies it bought during thecrisis. JP Morgan will pay roughly $2 billion in penalties thatapply to its own conduct during the years before the financialcrisis, and not any for problems it inherited from Bear StearnsCos or Washington Mutual Inc.
